As it's documented in the MQ Administration Guide
[http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E18930_01/html/821-2438/aeooq.html#scrolltoc](http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E18930_01/html/821-2438/aeooq.html#scrolltoc)

The ActivationSpec properties endpointExceptionRedeliveryXXX handles the case when a MDB onMessage() throws Exception;

For the case of MDB setRollbackOnly (e.g. in case of processing error in Java EE container managed transaction), please see #134;

For standalone client, OpenMQ's implementation in case of MessageListener.onMessage() throwing RuntimeException conforms to JMS specification 1.1 section 4.5.2 Asynchronous Delivery - that is, for transacted session, it's the client application controls the the message redelivery by Session.rollback. Therefore, this issue does not apply to OpenMQ standalone client.

